caption.text:
Ce soir, c'est un soir particulier.
Je renfile mon t-shirt Rockstar Mag' "Liberty93". Il s'agit de mon TOUT PREMIER t-shirt que je me suis fait en mars 2014. Rockstar Mag' avait un an seulement et c'était la première fois que je me montrai sur les réseaux sociaux. Un t-shirt symbolique qui est cher à mon coeur. Les années ont passé, je me rassure en me disant que s'il me sert un peu, c'est parce qu'il a subi les épreuves du temps et qu'il a rétréci au fil des conventions, au fil des vidéos et surtout au fil des lavages. Je remets ce t-shirt pour cette petite photo avec ce fameux trophée des 100.000 abonnés #YouTube. À l'époque de la photo, il y avait environ 55.000 abonnés sur YouTube, c'était avant l'arrêt de quatre ans de la chaîne. Des étoiles pleins les yeux, j'aspirais à un rêve, à une passion, plein de détermination. Mais en même temps, cette petite voix qui me disait que le rêve était peut-être impossible à atteindre. Fort heureusement, je suis un petit con qui n'écoute que lui, un peu trop casse-cou qui fonce et qui s'est souvent fait avoir. Entre désillusions et faux-espoirs ça n'a pas été toujours facile, il y a eu pas mal de doutes, mais je savais très bien que je ne devais rien lâcher. J'ai mis 5 ans à oser me lancer dans un nouveau projet. Puis en 8 mois, je me suis lancé dans 4 projets qui ont participé à changer ma vie. 
Liberty's Games en août 2018. Le Grand Tour #NSTG au même moment. Puis Naughty Dog Mag' en janvier 2019. Et enfin Presse-citron en mars 2019. Aujourd'hui, j'ai réussi l'objectif et mon rêve : vivre de ma passion. Et je suis tellement heureux et épanoui dans mon travail. 
Et j'ai tellement d'envie, de motivation, d'idées encore. Les années ont passé. Oui je n'ai plus 19 ans. Oui, le t-shirt est un peu délavé, et il a rétréci. Mais, 5 ans après, les étoiles sont toujours là dans les yeux, peut-être même plus nombreuses. Et plus que jamais, je suis fier, honoré et intimidé de voir tant de monde me suivre, ainsi que mes différentes communautés. Dingue de voir comment Naughty Dog Mag' monte vite. Alors merci, merci à tous. (Suite en commentaire)

Finally it's #backlogbattler time and this time it's Fist of the North Star Lost Paradise on PS4. A game where you play as Kenshiro in another non canon adventure where knowing characters does help. In the tutorial you take out Shin, then go to the city of Eden where you become it's protector. You befriend the captain of the guard, get a truck you can ride around the sandbox in, do odd jobs like bartending, healing and managing a host club. You get random battles with goons everywhere which build up exp. You get references to the anime and manga everywhere. It's a wander around fighty drivey smash people's skulls in affair that plays a lot like Yakuza. It's mindless and can rack up the time easily. It's a fun game and if you like the series you'll love it. If you allow things to get on top of you however the main story will take a back seat and you'll find yourself just wandering around or driving around the desert looking for people to kill and items to get in the wastes. It's a fun game and I think it's worth the £30 asking price. #sega #sony #gaming #gamer #retro #arcade #franchise #retrocollectiveeurope #pickups #3d #adventure #rpg #action #3d #atlus #fistofthenorthstar #hokutonoken #kenshiro #playstation #ps4 #gamestergram #videogames #gamersunite #gamecollector #gamersofinstagram #jackrabbitgamer

caption.text:
Pokémon: Let's Go Eevee (Switch) 
Pokémon has a universal appeal, but I think I'm about 20 years too old to be the target audience for this entry in the franchise.
Credit where credit is due, this remake of the first generation games excels in presentation. The game oozes charm, and is just how you'd picture the first games when you played them as a child: from the updated visuals and cutscenes, to the adorable interactions with your titular partner Pokémon, to your team following you outside their Pokéballs. Also a fun idea is that a second player can drop in and play co-op, with everything turning into a double battle. 
However, it feels like this game targets three demographics: those who have not played Pokémon since the first generation, those whose only experience with Pokémon is Pokémon Go, and very young children. Pokémon is not too complex of a game to begin with, but Let's Go is oversimplified to the point where it just stops being fun. Wild Pokémon encounters work just like Pokémon Go (except the wild Pokémon can flee at any moment), and battles are heavily weighed in the player's favour (I constantly found that my team was landing critical hits, dodging attacks, and enduring fatal blows, with flavour text saying it was because they didn't want me to be sad). I beat the game with zero effort using an underleveled team.
Another gripe I have is that we have explored Kanto in four different generations before even counting Let's Go. There is nothing new to see, no new area to explore, and as only the original 151 Pokémon are in the game (and also Meltan), I was hard-pressed to use Pokémon I had not previously had on my team in other games.
Similarly to the game itself, the Pokéball controller that came with the game is more style than substance. It's definitely a neat idea, and I did feel it improved the catching aspect as the motion controls felt more natural with a ball in hand, but the joystick also being the A button led to mis-selections as my attempt to click the button also moved the cursor.
Overall, I would only recommend this to people new to the Pokémon series, or who have not played since the original Game Boy games.
5.5/10

O eFootball PES 2020 entra em uma nova década de liderança na indústria dos simuladores de futebol com uma proposta ambiciosa de revolucionar o eFootball e introduzir o esporte a um público global.
A série PES dá continuidade a sua busca por realismo, trazendo várias mudanças significativas que emprestam a cada momento do jogo uma sensação de total liberdade e controle.
Sob a consultoria do lendário meio-campista Andrés Iniesta, a última edição da série foi moldada com total foco na imersão e na autenticidade.
Prepare-se para se fascinar com as novas habilidades de dribles e a física da bola que vão permitir aos jogadores ter mais controle do que nunca de suas ações dentro e fora de campo.
Assuma o lugar do treinador numa Liga Master completamente reformulada e viva a sensação única de orquestrar uma vitória extraordinária nos bastidores do teu próprio clube.
Espante-se com a energia da torcida enquanto você disputa o topo da tabela no novo modo competitivo Matchday.
E, finalmente, sinta os sons e os visuais dos campos reproduzidos de forma detalhada e nunca antes vistas graças às melhorias sonoras e gráficas.
